<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 12:41AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Towns and
northeastern Union Counties through 115 AM EDT...
At 1240 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Young Harris, or near
Hiawassee, moving southeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hiawassee, Blairsville, Young Harris, Brasstown Bald, Track Rock,
Gumlog, Macedonia, Titus, Mountain Scene and Alexanders Mill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
